---
const questions = [
  'Who are our best users?',
  'What makes them stay?',
  'Where do they drop off?',
  'What should we measure?',
  'How does our product actually grow?'
];
---

<section class="section-padding">
  <div class="container-content">
    <h2 class="heading-2 text-center mb-8">
      Teams can't answer the most basic growth questions
    </h2>

    <p class="body-text text-center mb-8">
      Every product team needs answers to these questions:
    </p>

    <!-- Questions Display -->
    <div class="max-w-md mx-auto bg-bg-elevated border border-border-default rounded-xl p-6 mb-8">
      <div class="space-y-3">
        {questions.map((q) => (
          <p class="text-text-muted text-sm">{q}</p>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Explanation -->
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center">
      <p class="body-text mb-4">
        The answers are scattered across tools, teams, and outdated documents.
      </p>
      <p class="body-text mb-4">
        Building this connected understanding — the <span class="text-text-primary font-medium">growth model</span> — requires weeks of consulting-grade work.
      </p>
      <p class="text-text-muted italic">
        Most teams get 30% done and give up. The growth model never gets finished.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
